data.chText: 货摊，摊位，售货亭（尤指集市上的）
data.enText: a table or small shop with an open front that people sell things from, especially at a market

data.chText: 集市上的货摊
data.enText: a market stall

data.chText: 牲畜棚；马厩；牛棚
data.enText: a section inside a farm building that is large enough for one animal to be kept in

data.chText: （房间内的）小隔间，淋浴室，洗手间
data.enText: a small area in a room, surrounded by glass, walls, etc., that contains a shower or toilet
the orchestra stalls
the orchestra

data.chText: （剧场的）正厅前排座位
data.enText: the seats that are nearest to the stage in a theatre

data.chText: 正厅第一排
data.enText: the front row of the stalls

data.chText: （教堂内）唱诗班和牧师的座位
data.enText: the seats at the front of a church where the choir (= singers) and priests sit

data.chText: （车辆发动机的）熄火；（车辆的）抛锚
data.enText: a situation in which a vehicle's engine suddenly stops because it is not getting enough power

data.chText: （飞机的）失速
data.enText: a situation in which an aircraft loses speed and goes steeply downwards

data.chText: （使）熄火，抛锚

before.enText: of a vehicle or an engine

data.enText: to stop suddenly because of a lack of power or speed; to make a vehicle or engine do this

data.chText: 汽车熄火打不着了。
data.enText: The car stalled and refused to start again.

data.chText: 我考驾照时车子熄了三次火。
data.enText: I stalled the car three times during my driving test.

data.chText: 故意拖延（以赢得时间）
data.enText: to try to avoid doing sth or answering a question so that you have more time

data.chText: 他们仍在拖时间，而不急于达成协议。
data.enText: They are still stalling on the deal.

data.chText: “你这是什么意思？”她问，故意拖延着时间。
data.enText: ‘What do you mean?’ she asked, stalling for time .

data.chText: 拖住（以赢得时间做某事）
data.enText: to make sb wait so that you have more time to do sth

data.chText: 你看能不能拖住她，我好把她的办公室搜查完。
data.enText: See if you can stall her while I finish searching her office.

data.chText: 暂缓；搁置；停顿
data.enText: to stop sth from happening until a later date; to stop making progress

data.chText: 旨在重新启动搁置的和平计划的努力
data.enText: attempts to revive the stalled peace plan

data.chText: 讨论再次停顿下来。
data.enText: Discussions have once again stalled.

means: 货摊，摊位，售货亭(尤指集市上的)
(房间内的)小隔间，淋浴室，洗手间
（教堂内）唱诗班和牧师的座位
拖住(以赢得时间做某事)

tr: a tactic used to mislead or delay
small area set off by walls for special use
small individual study area in a library
a booth where articles are displayed for sale
a compartment in a stable where a single animal is confined and fed
seating in the forward part of the main level of a theater
a malfunction in the flight of an aircraft in which there is a sudden loss of lift that results in a downward plunge
example: the plane went into a stall and I couldn't control it

tr: deliberately delay an event or action
example: she doesn't want to write the report, so she is stalling
The car stalled in the driveway
The inexperienced driver kept stalling the car

tr: cause an airplane to go into a stall
experience a stall in flight, of airplanes
put into, or keep in, a stall
postpone doing what one should be doing
example: He did not want to write the letter and procrastinated for days

value.def: If a process stalls, or if someone or something stalls it, the process stops but may continue at a later time.

example.ex: The Social Democratic Party has vowed to try to stall the bill until the current session ends.
example.tran: 社会民主党誓言要将该议案拖到本次议会会议结束之后。

example.ex: Negotiations remained stalled yesterday in New York.
example.tran: 昨天在纽约进行的谈判依然陷于停滞状态。

value.def: If you stall, you try to avoid doing something until later.

example.ex: Some parties have accused the governor of stalling...
example.tran: 有些党派指责州长在拖延时间。

example.ex: Thomas had spent all week stalling over his decision.
example.tran: 托马斯磨了整个星期，迟迟不想作出决定。

value.def: If you stall someone, you prevent them from doing something until a later time.

example.ex: Shop manager Brian Steel stalled the man until the police arrived.
example.tran: 商店经理布赖恩·斯蒂尔将那名男子拖住，直到警方赶到。

value.def: If a vehicle stalls or if you accidentally stall it, the engine stops suddenly.

example.ex: Your foot falls off the pedal and you stall the car.
example.tran: 你的脚离开踏板，汽车便会熄火。

value.def: A stall is a large table on which you put goods that you want to sell, or information that you want to give people.

example.tran: 出售当地水果的市场摊位

value.def: The stalls in a theatre or concert hall are the seats on the ground floor directly in front of the stage.
value.tran: (戏院、音乐厅的)正厅前排座位

value.boxr_value: in AM, use 美国英语用 orchestra

value.def: A stall is a small enclosed area in a room which is used for a particular purpose, for example a shower.
value.tran: (淋浴间等房间里的)小分隔间

value.boxr_value: in BRIT, usually use 英国英语通常用 cubicle
